radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 11 mm, fluid filled and has a thickened hyperemic mucosa. No free pelvic fluid. The visualized lung bases are clear of nodules, consolidations, or effusions. The liver enhances homogeneously with no focal nodules or lesions identified. The gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands are normal. The kidneys enhance and excrete contrast symmetrically. The colon has normal caliber and appearance. No ascites is present. The stomach and proximal small bowel are of normal caliber and appearance. There is no mesenteric or retroperitoneal adenopathy.
